    "form_header_text": "Rep. Correa FY27 Appropriations Request Form",
    "form_instructions_text": "Please fill out the following sections regarding your FY27 Appropriations request. For Community Project Funding requests, please fill out the separate form provided by our staff. Note: This form is based on guidance previously provided by the Appropriations Committee to Members of Congress. Required information and deadlines are subject to change once the committee issues updated guidance. Distinguishing types of requests: Program Request: a request to fund a specific program in the appropriations bill at a specified level. Example: Provide $x for the Gaining Early Awareness and Readiness for Undergraduate Programs. Language Request: a request to include specific bill or report language that does not direct funding to a particular entity but encourages, urges, or directs some type of action by an agency. Example: The Committee commends the Federal Office of Rural Health Policy for their efforts to expand the physician workforce in rural areas and supports continuation and expansion of the program to develop new rural residency programs, or Rural Training Programs.",
