            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "This programmatic request provides $9 billion for the NASA Science Mission Directorate to support decadal priorities and maintain American leadership in space exploration and research.",
            "rationale": "This combines the specific funding ask with the strategic mission of the SMD, focusing on decadal priorities and national leadership as outlined in the advocacy context.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_118647557:5e37c857e58b",
            "label": "List goals and expected outcomes.",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Restore NASA Science funding to $9 billion to ensure U.S. leadership in the 21st-century space race\n* Enable progress on National Academies Decadal Survey priorities, including the Dragonfly mission and planetary defense\n* Protect the aerospace workforce from further instability following the FY 2026 budget disruptions\n* Advance American economic competitiveness through cutting-edge R&D and technology transfer",
            "rationale": "Drawn from advocacy talking points regarding U.S. leadership, decadal priorities, and workforce stability.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_318904982:e384b8cff029",
            "label": "How will this benefit CA-46?",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Direct infusion of $10,937,354 in NASA Science obligations into CA-46 between FY 2023 and FY 2025\n* Support for Airborne Systems North America in Santa Ana, currently executing a $13.3M award for the Dragonfly mission parachute system\n* Sustaining high-tech manufacturing jobs at local firms like Superior Jig Inc ($1.9M) and Prudential Overall Supply\n* Investment in the local talent pipeline and STEM inspiration for the Orange County aerospace workforce",
            "rationale": "Cites specific spending data for CA-46, including $10.9M in total obligations and specific contracts for Airborne Systems North America and Superior Jig Inc in Santa Ana.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1455282563:c6b96712143d",
